{
  "text": "The NOS2A \u00c02.6 microsatellite has clearly arisen from the 5 0 end of an Alu element, which appears to have been inserted into a pre-existing MER repeat. Microsatellites often arise from repetitive elements, [CITATION_1] but usually from the 3 0 end. [CITATION_2] Comparative primate data [CITATION_3] show that the ",
